IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. FILEMERGER.
AUTHOR. SIMON MIKKELSEN.

* This program merges two files into one. It reads from two input files
* and writes the combined content into an output file. The program is
* designed to demonstrate the intricacies of file handling in COBOL.
* Pay close attention to the details, as the devil is in the details.

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE-1 ASSIGN TO 'INPUT1.TXT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE-2 ASSIGN TO 'INPUT2.TXT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'OUTPUT.TXT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE-1.
01  INPUT-RECORD-1 PIC X(100).

FD  INPUT-FILE-2.
01  INPUT-RECORD-2 PIC X(100).

FD  OUTPUT-FILE.
01  OUTPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  EOF-FLAG-1 PIC X VALUE 'N'.
01  EOF-FLAG-2 PIC X VALUE 'N'.
01  TEMP-VARIABLE PIC X(100).
01  GOLLUM-VARIABLE PIC X(100).
01  FRODO-VARIABLE PIC X(100).

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PROCEDURE.
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE-1
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE-2
    OPEN OUTPUT OUTPUT-FILE

    PERFORM UNTIL EOF-FLAG-1 = 'Y' AND EOF-FLAG-2 = 'Y'
     PERFORM READ-FILE-1
     PERFORM READ-FILE-2
     PERFORM WRITE-OUTPUT
    END-PERFORM

    CLOSE INPUT-FILE-1
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE-2
    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE

    STOP RUN.

READ-FILE-1.
    IF EOF-FLAG-1 NOT = 'Y'
     READ INPUT-FILE-1 INTO TEMP-VARIABLE
     AT END
         MOVE 'Y' TO EOF-FLAG-1
     NOT AT END
         MOVE TEMP-VARIABLE TO GOLLUM-VARIABLE
    END-IF.

READ-FILE-2.
    IF EOF-FLAG-2 NOT = 'Y'
     READ INPUT-FILE-2 INTO TEMP-VARIABLE
     AT END
         MOVE 'Y' TO EOF-FLAG-2
     NOT AT END
         MOVE TEMP-VARIABLE TO FRODO-VARIABLE
    END-IF.

WRITE-OUTPUT.
    IF EOF-FLAG-1 NOT = 'Y'
     MOVE GOLLUM-VARIABLE TO OUTPUT-RECORD
     WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD
    END-IF
    IF EOF-FLAG-2 NOT = 'Y'
     MOVE FRODO-VARIABLE TO OUTPUT-RECORD
     WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD
    END-IF.

